Data Type Compatibility in Data Federation

When federating data from external sources, the source data is converted to the corresponding Data Cloud data types. If the source data contains a data type that's not supported in Data Cloud, the column is ignored. Fields whose data types aren’t supported in Data Cloud get listed under the Unsupported Fields tab while creating a data stream. Boolean data types aren't supported in data federation.

Mapping Snowflake Data Types with Data Cloud Data Types
SNOWFLAKE DATA TYPE	DATA CLOUD DATA TYPE
NUMBER, DECIMAL, NUMERIC	Number
INT, INTEGER, SMALLINT, TINYINT, BYTEINT	Number
BIGINT	Number
FLOAT, FLOAT4, FLOAT8, DOUBLE, DOUBLE PRECISION, REAL	Number
VARCHAR, CHAR, CHARACTER, STRING, TEXT	Text
DATETIME, TIMESTAMP, TIMESTAMP_LTZ, TIMESTAMP_NTZ, TIMESTAMP_TZ	DateTime
DATE	Date
BOOLEAN	Not supported
TIME	Not supported
VARIANT, OBJECT, ARRAY, GEOGRAPHY, GEOMETRY	Not supported
BINARY, VARBINARY	Not supported
Mapping Google BigQuery Data Types with Data Cloud Data Types
GOOGLE BIGQUERY DATA TYPE	DATA CLOUD DATA TYPE
BIGNUMERIC	Number
FLOAT64	Number
INT64	Number
NUMERIC	Number
STRING	Text
DATE	Date
DATETIME	DateTime
TIMESTAMP	DateTime
BOOL	Not Supported
BYTES	Not Supported
TIME	Not Supported

TIMESTAMPZ	DateTime

GEOGRAPHY	Not Supported
HLLSKETCH	Not Supported
TIME	Not Supported

VARBYTE	Not Supported
